The paper deals with geometrical properties of the rank metric space and covering properties of rank metric codes, which are related to information theory and coding theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analytical expressions and bounds, which are related to algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper's focus on geometrical properties and bounds also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's use of geometrical properties and bounds in the design, decoding, and performance analysis of rank metric codes suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category.
